    • generateType1UUID

      public static UUID generateType1UUID()
      Generate Type 1 UUID A UUID represents a 128-bit value (36 Characters long) UUID version 1 is based on the current timestamp, measured in units of 100 nanoseconds from October 15, 1582, concatenated with the MAC address of the device where the UUID is created. If privacy is a concern, UUID version 1 can alternatively be generated with a random 48-bit number instead of the MAC address. Reference: https://www.baeldung.com/java-uuid
      Returns:
